  <h2>Life Before Conversion</h2>
  <p>
    After childhood, Paul was sent to Jerusalem to get an education at the school of Gamaliel. Little is known after this until the stoning of Saint Stephen, the first known martyr of the church. He was an active participant in the persecution of Christians, and later admitted to doing so. He continued these practices until about the age of 30.
  </p>
