  <h2>Conversion</h2>
  <p>
  Jesus appeared to Paul at around 31-36 AD as he was on his way to Damascus. He was blinded for three days. During these days he ate no food and drank no water, constantly praying to God. After a blessing, his sight returned and he became baptized. Following his conversion he devoted all of his life to God.
  </p>
