<div class="span8">
  <h2>Life After Conversion</h2>
  <p>
  Paul began to preach as soon as he was baptized. People were incredulous at the fact that Paul, a man who openly opposed Christianity, was preaching that Jesus was the son of God. Three years after his conversion he traveled to Jerusalem, meeting James and staying with Simon Peter for fifteen days. After this time Paul created some religious writings, but not much is known about this time of his life. It is known that around eleven years later he came back to Jerusalem.
  </p>
